Defendant Daejujuan K Spivey in court with attorney Parker Charles Mathers.  Defendant Daejujuan K Spivey in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms or body armor. Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  

 Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Mr. Arthur T.  

The Court imposed the following sentence:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 5 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2-1/2 years with credit for 70 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 2-1/2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but not for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.  The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of four (4) years.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 - No contact with Latoya W.;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Obtain high school diploma, HSED or GED;
 - No contact with co-actor Terrell Perkins;
 - Serve one (1) year condition time at the House of Correction, with Huber for work and school, and release to the Day Reporting Center; good time also allowed.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge,  costs, surcharges and disbursements as ordered.  Should defendant get revoked and sent to prison, Court ordered monies to be taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance to be paid while on Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Court ordered restitution set at zero, as there was none requested.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
